<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920218-0011</DOCNO><DOCID>920218-0011.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Visa International:   Counterfeit Losses Expected   To Double in Fiscal Year</HL><DATE>02/18/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11</SO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED FINANCIAL SERVICES, CREDIT INSTITUTIONS (FIS)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Visa International said it expects to report world-widecounterfeit losses nearly doubled in the year ending March31.   The San Francisco credit card concern said counterfeitlosses for the year are expected to be more than $100million, compared with $55 million the year before. If lossescontinue at the current rate, they could exceed $175 millionnext year, Visa said. The company said it is developing a newcomputer system for fraud detection that it hopes toimplement by the fall.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>